AdminAdded(address,address).details: Emitted when `superAdmin` adds a new admin.

Registered(address,uint8).details: Emitted when `approval` is registered in order to be approved or rejected.

params.newAdmin: The address of the new admin to be added Emits a {AdminAdded} event.

params.approval: Address of the approval that is going to be approved Emits a {Approved} event.

params.user: The address to be checked if it is pending

params.approval: Address of the approval that is going to be rejected. Emits a {Rejected} event.

params.revokedAdmin: The address of the admin to be revoked Emits a {AdminRevoked} event.

params.explorerLink: Link of the document hash in the explorer
params.ext: Extension of the document (ex: .pdf .doc .txt) Emits a {DocumentSubmitted} event.
params.ipfsLink: Link of the document hash in the IPFS
params.name: Name of the company/user.
params.validityEnd: Timestampt for the validity end, in unix
params.validityStart: Timestamp for the validity start, in unix

_isAdmin.details: Returns true if an account is an admin

_isSuperAdmin.details: Returns true if an account is an super admin

isApprovals.details: Mapping from address to a bool.
isApprovals.return: True if an account is approval.

addAdmin(address).notice: Adds a new admin to operate the contract

approve(address).notice: Approves a pending account for approval.

cancelDocument(uint256).notice: cancel a document only the approval

changeDocumentVisibility(uint256).notice: Change the visibility of a document if you are the owner of that document, if you aren't the owner, it's just returning false.

isAdmin(address).notice: Returns true if `account` is an admin
